  "name": "RPlog_Fleming_Tortures_Kyokusha",
  "title": "Fleming Tortures Kyokusha",
  "summary": "Aboard an Imperial ship, ISB Agent Korynn Fleming descends on the captured near-human Kyokusha, who lies recovering in the medical wing after a crash. Coldly cataloguing her alien features, he orders her strapped down for 'procedure twenty-three delta' over her protests that she saved Admiral Danik Kreldin's life and demanded fifty thousand credits only as a front to protect his pride. Fleming injects a serum that violently heightens all her senses, then fits her with an electrode halo and methodically administers escalating shocks to interrogate her about her loyalties and to 'recondition' her hatred of the Empire, while Dr. Lynae and Dr. Caiton observe and record her vitals. Despite Kyokusha's defiant insistence that she acted out of honor and free will rather than allegiance, Fleming presses the pain up to setting four of ten before relenting, vowing to consult Kreldin personally. He administers the reversal agent slowly to prolong her suffering and leaves her dazed and terrified, returned to her bed under guard.",
